'''Pieter Gerardus "Piet" van Katwijk''' (born 27 February 1950) is a retired Dutch cyclist who was active between 1969 and 1983. He competed at the [[1972 Summer Olympics]] and finished in eleventh place in the road race.<ref name=r1/><ref name=r2/> He won the [[Milk Race]] (1973) and [[Acht van Chaam]] (1974) as well as several stages of the [[Olympia's Tour]] (1970, 1971, 1972), [[Tour de Suisse]] (1976), [[Tour of Belgium]] (1976), [[Ronde van Nederland]] (1977) and [[Tour de Luxembourg]] (1977). 

His brothers [[Jan van Katwijk|Jan]] and [[Fons van Katwijk|Fons]] and nephew [[Alain van Katwijk|Alain]] were also professional cyclists.<ref name=r2/>

